<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8500 - REMOVE AND
        INSTALL - BUMPER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>BUMPER</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Bumper Removal</title>
            <para>The 8500 Series aerodynamic bumper is attached to the chassis bumper mounting brackets utilizing (4)
                four bolts.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Beginning at the upper two bolts, loosen bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove both lower bumper bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Supporting the bumper, remove the two remaining bolts. Remove bumper.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900611" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900611.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Bumper Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. UPPER BUMPER MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOWER BOLT LOCATION (PASSENGER SIDE SHOWN)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Bumper Install</title>
            <para>Beginning at the upper bolt hole of the steel bumper:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the bumper mounting holes with the mounting bracket holes.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert bolts in the upper holes, one driver side, one passenger side. Hand tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the lower bumper mounting holes and insert lower bolts, and hand tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Finish tightening the bumper bolts with socket to 68 - 75 Nm (50 - 55 lbf-ft).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
